<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the War
                                Shipping Administrator</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Land</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde
                                        Park</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-02">September 2, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for Admiral Land</hi></p>
                        <p>I have not heard anything about the proposed personnel if the Prime
                            Minister comes over but if he brings Lord Leathers you must, of course,
                            come to Quebec. I will let you know shortly. Meantime, will you keep
                            yourself in readiness to come to Quebec, leaving the ninth or tenth?</p>
                        <closer><signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>